messages.message: If I’m on dogfood, viewing “All Apps” and then I click on the IB icon at the top of the left pane, why does it establish a session to datadog? Seems like an unneeded delay.
clicking the IB icon takes you to the IB home page, and this datadog session is established for every new browser session with instabase
@Serena so going from the “All Apps” view back to the homepage requires a new browser session to be established? I’m not opening a new tab.
if you’re going to a new URL (unless you’re navigating within an IB app) or if you reload, a new browser session is established
Also, this request is handled asynchronously. It should have virtually no effect on page load time compared to when this request is not sent.
